Robert,
You beat me to it - I just got back to my computer and saw that I'd made a
typo previously. Intel 15 is version 15.3; we also have OpenMPI built
against it. So you can use:

module purge; module load intel/15.3 openmpi


Then the system knows where mpicxx is:

[jkrometi@brlogin2 ~]$ which mpicxx
/opt/apps/intel15_3/openmpi/1.8.4/bin/mpicxx


Let me know if you have other questions. I will see if I can also get
mvapich2 and Intel MPI modules added as options under Intel 15.3.

Thanks,
Justin

jkrometi@brlogin2 ~]$ module purge; module load intel/15.3 openmpi
[jkrometi@brlogin2 ~]$ module list
Currently Loaded Modules:
  1) intel/15.3    2) openmpi/1.8.4
[jkrometi@brlogin2 ~]$ which mpicxx
/opt/apps/intel15_3/openmpi/1.8.4/bin/mpicxx




Justin Krometis
Advanced Research Computing
http://www.arc.vt.edu
jkrometis@vt.edu

